            "text": "Output Drift"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Output drift occurs when an LLM's responses change systematically over time \u2014 becoming shorter, more verbose, more cautious, tonally different, or factually inconsistent \u2014 without any intentional change by the operator. Drift is particularly dangerous because it produces HTTP 200 responses; standard latency and error-rate dashboards are blind to it. Detecting drift requires monitoring the statistical properties of model outputs against a stable reference baseline."
          }
        ]
      },
